Selena Quintanilla Pérez (Selena Quintanilla Zamora, Lake Jackson, Texas, USA, April 16, 1971 - Corpus Christi, 31 March 1995), better known as Selena, was a Grammy Award-winning Mexican-American singer born in Texas, the Latin pop, as Texas-Mexican music including the cumbia and ranchera prominent figure.
